": "In conclusion, in this study we have shown that there is no", "bbox": [406.1, 707.8, 706.1, 719.9]}, {"text": "speciﬁc genotype that can be associated with M. pneumoniae", "bbox": [391.4, 722.5, 706.1, 734.7]}, {"text": "groups of asymptomatic individuals. This should provide more", "bbox": [57.5, 727.8, 372.2, 740.0]}, {"text": "virulence or asymptomatic carriage. In addition, we found", "bbox": [391.4, 737.2, 706.1, 749.4]}, {"text": "insight in the physiology of asymptomatic colonization of the", "bbox": [57.5, 742.5, 372.2, 754.7]}, {"text": "marked genetic diﬀerences between clinical isolates and the", "bbox": [391.4, 751.9, 706.1, 764.0]}, {"text": "human respiratory tract by M. pneumoniae.", "bbox": [57.5, 757.2, 269.6, 769.4]}, {"text": "reference strains, which indicated that the latter strains may", "bbox": [391.4, 766.6, 706.1, 778.7]}, {"text": "Another important issue to consider is whether or not", "bbox": [72.2, 771.9, 372.2, 784.1]}, {"text": "not be regarded as appropriate representatives of circulating", "bbox": [391.4, 781.3, 706.1, 793.4]}, {"text": "M. pneumoniae was the actual causative agent of the RTI in the", "bbox": [57.5, 786.6, 372.2, 798.8]}, {"text": "M. pneumoniae strains.", "bbox": [391.4, 796.0, 505.1, 808.1]}, {"text": "diﬀerent groups of symptomatic patients that were included in", "bbox": [57.5, 801.3, 372.2, 813.5]}, {"text": "this study. Recent studies have indicated that multiple pathogens", "bbox": [57.5, 816.0, 372.2, 828.2]}, {"text": "can be present in the respiratory tract of children and adults AUTHOR CONTRIBUTIONS", "bbox": [57.5, 830.2, 590.2, 845.5]}, {"text": "with RTI (Spuesens et al., 2013; Biesbroek et al., 2014a,b; Dickson", "bbox": [57.5, 845.4, 372.2, 857.6]}, {"text": "et al., 2014). As a consequence, we cannot rule out that pathogens ES, AV, and CV initiated the study and were responsible for the", "bbox": [57.5, 860.1, 706.1, 872.3]}, {"text": "other than M. pneumoniae might have caused the symptomatic original design. ES, RB, CK, KM, and TH all contributed to the", "bbox": [57.5, 874.8, 706.1, 887.0]}, {"text": "“phenotype” in at least some of the included symptomatic execution of the study (speciﬁcally by retrieving patient clinical", "bbox": [57.5, 889.5, 706.1, 901.7]}, {"text": "patients. Clearly, this may have obstructed the identiﬁcation of information, performance of the culture of the M. pneumoniae", "bbox": [57.5, 904.2, 706.1, 916.4]}, {"text": "potential genomic features that allow discrimination between strains, DNA isolation and sequencing). RJ provided the clinical", "bbox": [57.5, 918.9, 706.1, 931.1]}, {"text": "Frontiers in Microbiology | www.frontiersin.org 6 October 2016 | Volume 7 | Article 1701", "bbox": [57.5, 951.8, 706.1, 960.8]}]}